title: For Sale:  Yugo 59 SKS 7.62x39 and AMMO
postcontent: For sale is a factory fresh rearsenaled Yugo 59 SKS.  This is a C serial 59, not a 59/66.  These are much less common than the 59/66 with the grenade spigot and grenade sights.  These are much more similar to the original Russian design, and have a much better front end weight than the 59/66.  They produced fewer than 100,000 59s, as opposed to the multiple millions of the 59/66.This gun came in a crate with 4 others fresh from the arsenal where they were likely refurbished (these could be brand new unissued, but I expect it was rebuilt at the arsenal).  As the pictures show, the gun is basically brand new.  The internals are fresh, the gun behaves perfectly and the finish looks great.  The gun even has a VERY discreet import mark under the barrel to a local importer in Knoxville TN! (As opposed to some of the guns coming in recently with a CENTURY INTERNATIONAL billboard on the side).Included are the factory log books and original cleaning rod, cleaning kit in the buttstock, magazine pouch, sling and oil can.  This is in the same condition it rode across the boat, other than the maybe 100 rounds I have shot through it and a good cosmoline removal.Also included is a lot of ammunition as I am getting out of the 7.62x39 game for a while.Roughly (erring conservatively, there is more included than inventoried but I am tossing it all in)200 rounds of FMJBT Golden Tiger (best steel case 7.62x39 out there) in boxes170 rounds of FMJBT Golden Tiger on Circle 31 stripper clips240 rounds of Brown Bear JSPAll in a 30 cal ammo can (except what wouldn't fit).So at least 600 rounds of top shelf 7.62x39 and stripper clips are included. I will not sell the gun without the ammunition; I will no longer have a gun to shoot it out of. However I will sell the ammunition seperately if someone wants it first; $150.Compare my price with the stack of ammunition to the TWO Yugo 59s on Gunbroker right now: $900 and $600.Not interested in trades unless it is a Ruger Precision Rifle in 6.5 Creedmoor as this is what I am selling the SKS to fund (I would include cash toward the RPR obviously). title: For Sale:  Lorcin L380
postcontent: The Lorcin L380 brought the beef to the cheap pocket gun market during its brief production from 1988 until 1996. It is the direct ancestor to the popular Hi Point 380HC Pistol. Manufacturer was Lorcin Engineering Co. of Mira Loma, California. Type is single action only, striker fired, blowback action semi-automatic pocket pistol, with main safety only. Construction is steel barrel sleeve, firing pin, and internal parts, with zinc alloy / zamak or pot metal barrel shroud, frame, trigger, and magazine release. Grip panels are polymer. Barrel is 3 1/2 inch with six groove right hand 1:16 rifling. Sight is blade front and raised fixed notch rear cast into the slide itself, with white polymer 3 dot inserts. Chambering is .380 ACP Caliber, and its steel magazine holds 7 rounds, 7 + 1 fully loaded capacity. Note the European style butt mounted magazine release and type two square trigger guard front. Trigger is .195 polymer smooth face, with left side mounted lever safety. Trigger pull is 7 1/2 pound vicinity. Weight empty is 31 ounces. Finish is black anodized; and black trigger and magazine release.  Surface detractions are minimal with some scratches on the trigger and some scuffing on the handguards; the magazine is a little difficult to remove.

The 92FS consistently bests the US military requirement of a 10-shot group of 3” or less at 50 meters (just short of 55 yards). While this type of  match-grade accuracy is impressive, it is no magic. At Beretta, we know that absolutely precise tolerances keep performance consistent shot after shot—which not only gives the 92FS its extraordinary accuracy, but it makes all factory parts interchangeable within the same model. Couple this to the ability to reliably feed every variety of commercial ammunition, and it is easy to understand why the 92FS remains the best pistol in its class. Its Bruniton finish is highly resistant to sweat and corrosion, and after shooting, a tool-free disassembly latch makes it a snap to take the pistol apart for cleaning. These and countless other useful features make the 92FS the choice of military and police professionals all over the world, as well as individuals wanting the absolute best for sport or self-protection.

title: For Sale:  Tactical Thermal Imaging FLIR SHIELD Tent, Survival Shelter, Blanket Poucho MULTICAM Tarp
postcontent:
Designed to reduce, confuse, and eliminate your thermal heat signature.
This is a quality handcrafted piece of gear made here in AZ. This tarp is known as a thermal shield or thermal block shaped into an 'Alpha Tent'. The primary purpose is to hide your heat signature from thermal imaging (FLIR). This is achieved by constructing the two inner layers from Heatsheets LDPE-4 reflective space blankets, made by SOL. These 'space' or 'survival' blankets are not your standard cheap mylar ones, but are much more durable and quiet. You must maintain an air gap between your skin and the material otherwise eventually you will heat up the fabric from direct touch. The two outside layers are made from waterproof 70d ripstop nylon in multicam (top) and coyote brown (bottom). The alpha tents shape is low profile and easy to conceal. Tarp weighs only 1lb.13.9oz!
This tent was designed with maximum adjustability in mind. In each corner there are 2 webbing pockets that the tent poles can be inserted into to adjust height, or for a quicker adjustment, there is shock cord running through the ends that can be cinched up to adjust the height and ventilation. As seen in the picture you can cinch up one side for observation and as a shooting/observation position if needed. There is a Velcro strap inside that secures and centers the tent poles. Mil-spec nylon webbing and thread is used and attachments are all box stitched.
The 18in tent poles are top of the line made by Easton and crafted out of lightweight aluminum which are scratch-resistant with a hard-anodized surface (12.7oz for all poles!). Standard sized shock cord is used inside the poles. Poles can be easily cut shorter if desired. Easton poles are used extensively on Everest expeditions and for USMC combat shelters.
The tent can be used as a stand alone tarp strung up with paracord/stakes in countless ways but is designed to be used with the poles as an alpha tent. Eight webbing loops are provided and one on top for many options to secure the tarp. Can be used as a survival blanket, ground tarp, makeshift litter, poncho, emergency shelter, or upside down gear raft. Look up alpha tent and thermal shield for more details on the concepts. Works against handheld, drone, or aircraft mounted thermal imaging. Add foliage/brush/ghillie on top for greater shape concealment. Can be deployed in under 90 seconds.
Tarp is appx 5ft x 8ft. Two available, more may be made in May. I live in Buckeye, come to west valley to meet.
Video link below, shows just a single layer space blanket working decently well against an apache.
